          "content": "Full and Sparse Snapshots<br><br>The content of snapshots generated by ALTER PLUGGABLE DATABASE ... SNAPSHOT depends on the underlying file system. If the underlying file system supports sparse copies, then the PDB-level snapshots are sparse. Only the first PDB-managed PDB snapshot is full. Otherwise, the PDB snapshots contain full copies of the data files. The snapshot includes other files necessary to create a PDB from the snapshot.<br><br>If the file system supports sparse files, then all PDB snapshots in the carousel except the first one are sparse. The source PDB can remain in read/write mode. Sparse files significantly reduce the carousel storage space.",
