          "content": "I think that correct answers are A -B - C<br>Below I have extracted the line for each question from the following Oracle document: https://docs.oracle.com/en/database/oracle/oracle-database/21/bradv/rman-block-media-recovery.html#GUID-C1164158-496C-4D8A-8A06-D343935FC3B9<br><br>A - True - affected data files to remain online during recovery<br>B - True - Flashback Database must be enabled on the target database for RMAN to search the flashback logs for good copies of corrupt blocks.<br>C - True - No subsequent read of the block is successful until the block is recovered<br>D - False - You can perform block recovery only on blocks that are marked corrupt or that fail a corruption check.<br>E - False - The target database must run in ARCHIVELOG mode and be open or mounted with a current control file<br>F - False - Logical corruption checking is disabled by default. You can turn it.",
